# Implementation philosophy

- **Avoid goldplating** — simplest fix that meets the requirement; don’t add layers for hypothetical futures.
- **Stop when complexity spikes** — nested conditionals or “framework for one call site” → refactor or simplify first.
- **Ask when ambiguous** — two divergent patterns in the codebase? Prefer aligning with maintainer direction over inventing a third pattern.
- **Unify inconsistencies** — merge duplicate approaches; don’t build abstractions that permanently support both unless migration is in progress.

Overlaps with `.cursor/rules/elegance.mdc` (structure) and `.cursor/rules/ts-code-quality.mdc` (types/style) by design.
